cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on image compression, which is a fundamental low-level image processing task, and aims to produce compressed images that are consistent in both appearance and perception. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a pre-trained CNN to extract features and employs the maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) to minimize the difference between feature distributions, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a compression network that can generate images that can be well recognized by pre-trained machine learning models, indicating that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of MMD to minimize feature distribution differences suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
